INORDER TRAVERSAL OF A BINARY TREE

Inorder traversal of a binary tree means visiting nodes in the following order:

Traverse the left subtree
Visit the root node
Traverse the right subtree

TASK

You are given a binary tree. Your task is to print the nodes of the tree using inorder traversal.

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer N
N is the number of nodes in the binary tree

The next (N - 1) lines describe the edges of the tree
Each line contains three values:
pi ci Ri

where
pi is the parent node value
ci is the child node value
Ri represents the relationship
L means ci is the left child of pi
R means ci is the right child of pi

OUTPUT FORMAT

Print N space-separated integers representing the inorder traversal of the binary tree

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ N ≤ 10000
1 ≤ pi, ci ≤ 100000
Ri is either L or R
All node values are distinct

SAMPLE INPUT

5
1 2 L
1 3 R
3 4 L
3 5 R

SAMPLE OUTPUT

2 1 4 3 5

EXPLANATION

The inorder traversal follows left subtree, root, then right subtree.
So the output sequence is 2 1 4 3 5.
